public class ModifyPartForm extends Object implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
Author:
Huy G To The ModifyPartForm class allows a selected part from the main menu to be modified, this means changing its parameters, and changing whether its outsourced/inhouse

      *****FUTURE ENHANCEMENT***** On the saving the modified part to the menu I think a better way of improving on this is being able to modify all the parts at once through the main menu without having to go to another screen and populating text fields. It would make it alot more intuitive and allow the user to modify multiple parts at once. I also think out of all the methods that I've made and all the incorporations of things I've learned throughout the course my implementation of saving the modified part is probably the ugliest work I've made. It works 100% but if you look through it you can tell its not the most optimized way to do it and If i spent more time on it I could for sure improve on it and make it be way cleaner and less wordy. It was one of my first challenges throughout the program and as I went through further and further I got better along the way.
